## Composition Architecture

### Avoid Boolean Prop Proliferation
Don't add `isSmall`, `isBordered`, `isAlt` flags. Use explicit variant components or `children` composition.
```tsx
// Wrong
<StoryCard isSmall isBordered />
// Correct
<StoryCardCompact />
// Or compose
<StoryCard><StoryCard.Heading>...</StoryCard.Heading></StoryCard>
```

### Compound Components with Context (React 19)
```tsx
const EventsContext = createContext<EventsContextValue | null>(null);

function EventsProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const [expandedId, setExpandedId] = useState<string | null>(null);
  return <EventsContext value={{ state: { expandedId }, actions: { setExpandedId } }}>{children}</EventsContext>;
}

function EventRow({ id, title }: { id: string; title: string }) {
  const { state, actions } = use(EventsContext!);  // use() not useContext()
  return <div onClick={() => actions.setExpandedId(id)}>{title}</div>;
}
```

**State must represent ground truth.** Store `isVisible: boolean`, derive `opacity` from it. Never store visual output values.

### Children Over Render Props
```tsx
// Correct — composable, readable
<StoryCard>
  <StoryCard.Heading>Our Story</StoryCard.Heading>
  <StoryCard.Body>...</StoryCard.Body>
</StoryCard>
```

### React 19 APIs
- `ref` is a regular prop — no `forwardRef` wrapper
- `use(Context)` replaces `useContext(Context)` — can be called conditionally
- `<MyContext value={...}>` replaces `<MyContext.Provider value={...}>`

